nistrative practices and shifting power relations of the period, Morality Tales argues that it was only in local interpretation that legal rules acquired vitality and meaning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSex and lawxHistory. 0aWomen (Islamic law)zTurkeyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  a16th century.  aadministrative.  aanalysis.  aanatolian.  aclass issues.  acommunity.  acourt cases.  acourtroom.  adomestic.  afamily issues.  afamily life.  agender issues.  ajustice.  alaw.  alegal issues.  alocal justice.  amiddle east.  amiddle eastern.  amorality.  aottoman empire.  apower relations.  apower.  aproperty.  apunishment.  aself representation.  asocial hierarchy.  asultan.  aviolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022890040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092697440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520926974423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520926974/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY